# Font & Icon Rules (ShuttleUp Frontend)

## Text Font

- The project uses **"Be Vietnam Pro"** (Google Font, Vietnamese-optimized) loaded via `style.css` template.
- Manager layout: `var(--mgr-font)` = `'Be Vietnam Pro', 'Segoe UI', system-ui, -apple-system, sans-serif`.
- Admin layout: `var(--adm-font)` — same stack.
- **NEVER** add a custom `font-family` declaration in new CSS. Let elements inherit from their layout ancestor, or use the CSS variable (`var(--mgr-font)`, `var(--adm-font)`).

```css
/* ❌ BAD — overrides Be Vietnam Pro, breaks Vietnamese diacritics */
.my-component {
  font-family: system-ui, -apple-system, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, sans-serif;
}

/* ✅ GOOD — inherits Be Vietnam Pro from parent */
.my-component {
  font-size: 14px;
  font-weight: 600;
}

/* ✅ GOOD — explicit variable when needed */
.my-component {
  font-family: var(--mgr-font);
}
```

## Icons

| Context | Library | How it's loaded |
|---------|---------|-----------------|
| Manager / Admin pages | **Feather** icons (`feather-*` classes) | `<link>` to `/assets/css/feather.css` in `index.html` |
| Player / Landing pages | **FontAwesome** (`fa-*`, `fas`, `far`, `fab` classes) | `<link>` to `/assets/plugins/fontawesome/css/all.min.css` in `index.html` |

- **NEVER** install `@fortawesome/fontawesome-free` (or any FontAwesome package) via npm. The npm bundle injects `@font-face` rules through Vite that override Vietnamese font rendering.
- FontAwesome is loaded as a **static CSS file** from `public/assets/plugins/` — this keeps it outside the Vite bundle and avoids font conflicts.
- **Webfonts must exist**: The CSS references `../webfonts/*.woff2`. These files must be present at `public/assets/plugins/fontawesome/webfonts/`. **Without them icons show as blank squares (□)**. The woff2 files are committed to git (required static assets).
  - To refresh webfonts: temporarily `npm install @fortawesome/fontawesome-free`, copy `node_modules/@fortawesome/fontawesome-free/webfonts/*.woff2` → `public/assets/plugins/fontawesome/webfonts/`, then `npm uninstall @fortawesome/fontawesome-free`.
- If you need a new icon, pick from Feather (Manager/Admin) or FontAwesome (Player/Landing) — do not add a third icon library.

## Modal z-index

- `.mgr-topbar` has `z-index: 1030` with `position: sticky`.
- `.mgr-page` creates a stacking context at `z-index: 1`.
- Any modal inside Manager/Admin layout **must** use `createPortal(..., document.body)` and `z-index >= 1100` to appear above the topbar.
